From: Growth Habitat build assistant
Subject: [PATCH] Data layer + live Profile and Directions pages

The app stops being a mockup. Profile and Directions are now fully editable
with autosave-on-blur. The Command Center pulls live data from the store
instead of hard-coded constants. Twelve files: 4 modified, 7 new, 1 config.

What's new
----------

src/types/entities.ts — TypeScript types for every entity in the app.
Profile, Direction, Conversation, Opportunity, Hypothesis, Reflection,
Pattern, plus the AppData top-level shape. Adds:
  - evidenceStrength: "weak" | "medium" | "strong" on Conversation and Opportunity
  - trustSignal: "forming" | "not_enough_signal" | "concern" on Conversation
  - taggedEnergyGains/taggedEnergyDrains: string[] on Conversation
    (data hooks for cross-page Profile-as-measurement-reference)
  - workWithOnHardProblem: yes/no/maybe on Conversation (the "would I
    work with them on a hard problem next month" check)
  - Hypothesis with confidence (1-10) and isCurrent flag for versioning

src/lib/seed.ts — Achim's actual seed content, faithfully transcribed:
ten strengths in his words, five energy gains, five drains, three
non-negotiables, five thrive environments, three avoid environments,
seven directions with hypotheses and initial scores, one current
hypothesis at confidence 5.

src/lib/scoring.ts — Pure functions. directionAverage, conversationEnergyGain,
conversationSignalAverage, opportunityFitScore, weightedEvidenceCount
(weak=1, medium=2, strong=4), countByStrength, rankDirections,
strongestDirection, rankConversationsByEnergyGain, bestRecentConversation,
commandStats. No state, no side effects.

src/lib/storage.ts — Single-key localStorage adapter with migration support.
load(), save(), reset(), exportJSON(), importJSON(), downloadJSON(). The
SCHEMA_VERSION constant is what enables future format changes without
losing data. Swap this one file for a Cloudflare Workers + D1 client
later, no other file changes.

src/lib/store.tsx — React context wrapping the storage layer. StoreProvider
plus hooks: useStore, useProfile, useDirections, useConversations,
useOpportunities, useCurrentHypothesis. Autosave runs on every mutation
with a 200ms debounce so a burst of edits batches into one save. Quiet
saved-indicator state available via the saving flag.

src/pages/Profile.tsx — Full editing surface. Eleven sections: working
identity, positioning, current/desired, strengths, working style, energy
gains, energy drains, thrive environments, avoid environments, non-
negotiables. Each section uses AutosaveInput / AutosaveTextarea /
AutosaveList — commits happen on blur. Quiet saved indicator in the topbar.

src/pages/Directions.tsx — Full editing surface for the seven directions.
Each direction is a collapsible card with: name (autosave), status pill
(click to cycle through active/explore/park/avoid), score row (7
dimensions, click-to-set 1-10), description, hypothesis, notes. Cards
are ordered by averageScore descending; avoided directions appear in a
separate group at the bottom. Add via prompt, delete with confirm.
Includes inline DecisionLegend defining pursue/explore/park/avoid.

What's modified
---------------

src/components/Primitives.tsx — Adds AutosaveInput, AutosaveTextarea,
AutosaveList, AutosaveScore, StatusPill primitives. Existing components
unchanged.

src/App.tsx — Wraps everything in StoreProvider. The AppShell now reads
profile.name, profile.currentHypothesis, and conversation count from the
live store instead of hard-coded constants.

src/pages/CommandCenter.tsx — Connected to live store data. Strongest
direction, best recent conversation, watch-out, stats band, and "next
step" suggestion all derive from real entities. Discovery phase landscape
auto-detects which phase Achim is in based on what data exists. The
auto-suggested next step shows its basis ("Why: this direction scores
8.1 but has 0 conversations logged"). When a tile has no data to show,
it renders a helpful empty state instead of fake content.

src/pages/StubPage.tsx — No functional change, just confirmed unchanged.

tsconfig.json — Bumps target/lib from ES2020 to ES2022 to enable Array.at()
which the hypothesis history code uses.

Apply with:
    git apply 0003-data-layer-profile-directions.patch

Or with plain patch:
    patch -p1 < 0003-data-layer-profile-directions.patch

Verify:
    npm run build
    npm run dev

Then visit /, /profile, /directions and confirm:
- Profile fields edit, blur, save quietly
- Directions cards expand, scores click to set, status cycles
- Command Center reflects your edits in real time

